[00:00.56] She only ever walks to count her steps,
[00:07.84] Eighteen strides and she stops to abide by the law that she herself has set -
[00:15.59] That eighteen steps is one complete set, and before the next nine right and nine left
[00:22.99] She looks up at the blue and whispers to all of the above:
[00:30.43] 'Don't let me drown, don't breath alone, no kicks no pangs no broken bones.
[00:38.40] Never let me sink, always feel at home, no sticks no shanks and no stones.
[00:46.56] Never leave it too late, always enjoy the taste of the great grey world of hearts.'
[00:54.89] As all dogs everywhere bark, 'It's worth knowing
[01:02.97] Like all good fruit the balance of life is in the ripe and ruin.'